<div id="review_2994434693" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2994434693" />
    <a title="Tom Reeves" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5889912-tom-reeves"><img alt="Tom Reeves" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1433099509p2/5889912.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2994434693?book_show_action=true">Sep 29, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tom Reeves" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tom Reeves" href="/user/show/5889912-tom-reeves">Tom Reeves</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780345349286" href="/book/show/1666.On_Heroes_and_Tombs">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2994434693" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12255613866257765090">I don&apos;t know where to begin on this. Some parts are 5 stars and some are much less. I am not sure if 3 stars is the right rating.... I was really excited to read this book and perhaps that ruined it for me. I get the feeling that I didn&apos;t quite get the book, perhaps I was thinking it was something else. <br/><br/>It starts brilliantly but eventually drags. The Report On The Blind was at times entertaining and crazy but also dragged for me and except the last few pages it felt repetitive.<br/><br/>There are some bea</span>
  <span id="freeText12255613866257765090" style="display:none">I don't know where to begin on this. Some parts are 5 stars and some are much less. I am not sure if 3 stars is the right rating.... I was really excited to read this book and perhaps that ruined it for me. I get the feeling that I didn't quite get the book, perhaps I was thinking it was something else. <br /><br />It starts brilliantly but eventually drags. The Report On The Blind was at times entertaining and crazy but also dragged for me and except the last few pages it felt repetitive.<br /><br />There are some beautifully haunting passages that really stick with you. One where the characters swim in the ocean during a storm is amongst the best chapters I have ever read. There are a good amount of quality moments like this throughout and Sabato covers a lot of ground.<br /><br />Despite these nuggets of gold and a great final few pages I felt slightly disappointed at the end and glad to move onto something new. Maybe it just wasn't the right time for me to read this, maybe I will try again one day because there is definitely incredible talent here.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12255613866257765090" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
